    <div class="post-container" id="fpc-2806238">
                      
		<div class="post" id="post-2806238">
		<div class="long">
			<div class="head">
									<div class="options">
						<a href="javascript:;" onclick="togglePostFold(event,2806238)" class="btn btn-default btn-small btn-sm">Fold</a>
					</div>
								<div class="title" id="post-title-2806238">
																		
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/sunnyclockwork" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1621343); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1621343&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610203735" alt="SunnyClockwork" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1621343)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/sunnyclockwork" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1621343); return false;" >SunnyClockwork</a></span> <span class="odate time_1493562842 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">30 Apr 2017 14:34</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2806238">
									

<p>Basically, I saw this awesome tale, <a href="/the-parables-of-pseudo-nadox">The Parables of Pseudo-Nadox</a>, and think, hey, I should write some parables of SCPverse too! But instead I'm gonna write like lengthy Chinese text first and then translate them, because that will surely make it look authentic :D (Also that I can recycle all these old snippets I wrote.)</p>
<p>Great thanks to Lex1nat0r, Metaphysician, Conwell, Roget, Dora, Overandover, SpectralDragon, MrWrong, minmin, BitVyper, TheRaven, ZacharyMaxwell, Dr_Leonard, djkaktus, Vacuum, and all others who read the tale.</p>
<p>Art by me :3</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;List&nbsp;of&nbsp;SCP&nbsp;&amp;&nbsp;Myth/Legend&nbsp;references</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;List&nbsp;of&nbsp;SCP&nbsp;&amp;&nbsp;Myth/Legend&nbsp;references</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>The legend of Liu Bang slaying a white serpent: <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Emperor_Gaozu_of_Han#Insurrection_against_the_Qin_dynasty">https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Emperor_Gaozu_of_Han#Insurrection_against_the_Qin_dynasty</a></p>
<p><strong>About the Gods</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Fuxi/Father Serpent/伏羲 - Mekhane</li>
<li>Nüwa/Mother Dragon/女娲 - Yaldabaoth</li>
<li>Qilin/麒麟 - <a href="/scp-2845">SCP-2845</a> - THE DEER</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li>Pangu/盘古 - Chinese creation god: <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pangu">https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pangu</a> (&quot;天地始如鸡子&quot; based on &quot;天地混沌如鸡子&quot; from 《三王历纪》)</li>
<li>Guixu/归墟 - A bottomless pit in Chinese myth where all water eventually end up to</li>
<li>Nine Children/九子 - In Chinese myth, the dragon spawns nine different beasts: <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nine_sons_of_the_dragon">https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nine_sons_of_the_dragon</a></li>
<li>Taisui/太岁 - A invented planet opposing Jupiter: <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tai_Sui">https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tai_Sui</a></li>
</ul>
<p><strong>About the Kingdoms</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Kingdom of Apes/猿之国 - <a href="/scp-1000">SCP-1000</a> - Bigfoot</li>
<li>Xia Dynasty/夏 - <a href="/scp-2481">SCP-2481</a> - Kill the Suns</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>About the Kings</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>King of Ajia/阿伽之王 - <a href="/scp-701">SCP-701</a> - The Hanged King's Tragedy</li>
<li>Three Lords of Death/三阎罗 - Brothers Death (<a href="/scp-1440">SCP-1440</a> - The Old Man from Nowhere &amp; <a href="/death-and-the-doctors-hub">Death and the Doctors Hub</a>)</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li>Yulü/郁垒 - Chinese god in charge of capturing ghosts/souls</li>
<li>Yama/阎摩: <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Yama">https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Yama</a></li>
<li>Kshitigarbha/地藏: <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kshitigarbha">https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kshitigarbha</a></li>
</ul>
<p><strong>About the Beasts</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Yang/殃君 - Grand Karcist Ion (<a href="/sarkicism-hub">Sarkicism Hub</a>)</li>
<li>Daevas/狄瓦 - <a href="/scp-140">SCP-140</a> - An Incomplete Chronicle</li>
<li>Bumo/不末 - Bumaro (<a href="/church-of-the-broken-god-hub">Church of the Broken God Hub</a>)</li>
<li>Yaluo/压罗 - <a href="/scp-2095">SCP-2095</a> - The Siege of Gyaros</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>About Men</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Panjia/盘甲 - A very much headcanon version of Pangloss from a tale I never get to properly revise and post ._.</li>
<li>Mechanical soilders/机巧兵俑 &amp; a flying ship/飞舟 - <a href="/scp-580">SCP-580</a> - Shi Huang Ti's Five Heaven Chariot</li>
<li>&quot;He then sank the palace into the ground, and left the emperor with no escape despite his eternal life.&quot; - <a href="/scp-2101">SCP-2101</a> - The Imperial Army</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li>Jianmu/建木 - A tree from the Chinese myth that serves as a bridge between heaven and earth</li>
<li>Epang Palace/阿房宫: <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Epang_Palace">https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Epang_Palace</a></li>
<li>Shu Huang Ti's burning of books: <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Burning_of_books_and_burying_of_scholars">https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Burning_of_books_and_burying_of_scholars</a></li>
<li>Xu Fu/徐福: <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Xu_Fu">https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Xu_Fu</a></li>
</ul>
<p>The things Panjia mentioned about the ancient times are actually: Tower of Babel, Eden, and Kunlun: <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kunlun_Mountains#Mythology">https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kunlun_Mountains#Mythology</a></p>
<p>Yufu/鱼凫 &amp; Cancong/蚕丛 are both mythical kings of Shu state, but here I'm actually adapting them the whole Xia series, and have little to do with the actual myth ._.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>

