														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2806886">
									

<p>The Xia Dynasty stuff has always been interesting to me, as it takes a fair amount of the preexisting Sarkic and CotBG stuff and places it in a setting that is usually not used that often outside the Xia skips and tales, to my knowledge. Each segment here reads as a nice tiny bite of mythology, doing a good job of worldbuilding without overstaying its welcome. On top of that, the art included before each section really does add a nice touch of flavor.</p>
<p>I really liked reading this as a draft, and I like it now. +1.</p>

